snippet.textDisplay: It's interesting how much the symptoms vary. For me I had bad thirst, feeling like there is water in my ears and very severe body pain, especially in my back. If it wasn't for a positive test I wouldn't of thought I had covid at all

snippet.textDisplay: i got it very lucky, just a fever, sore throat and a cough. no loss of taste, no aches, nothing serious

snippet.textDisplay: For me it started with back pain, later in the first day it started a fever, with pain in the entire chest area, and during the first night i had severe headache and even allucinations. By the second day i had almost no pain, was a little less feverish, but i felt so tired and fatigued that i went to a hospital, but i wasn't even diagnosed by covid, so i went back for work. By the third day onwards, it appeared those most common symptoms like sore throat, cough, and some fatigue/lazyness, and henceforth i started suspecting it could be covid and went again to the hospital and finally being diagnosed, and took the determined precautions and cares for the next days.
